<div class="container">
  <div class="jumbotron">
    <h2>BMR - Basal Metabolic Rate</h2>
    <br />
    <button id="showButton" onclick="showDescription()" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block">What is BMR? (click me)</button>
    <div class = "bmrInfo">
    <hr />
    <p>
      UPDATE: Your BMR is the amount of calories you burn just to be you.
    </p>
     <p>That means your
      profile (i.e. height, age, weight, gender).
    </p>
    <p>For example, someone who is 200 pounds will, by default, burn more calories than someone who weighs 150 pounds.
    </p>
    </p>
    <p>
      Once you find your BMR, you then need to factor in your exercise levels.
    </p>
    <p>
      Once that is factored in, you will know how many calories you need to consume
      to maintain, lose, or gain weight.
    </p>
    <p>The calculator below will help you figure our your numbers</p>
    <br /><br />
  </div>
  <br /><br />
  <div class="calculation">
    <form action="" id="profileForm">
      <fieldset>
        <legend>ENTER YOUR INFO BELOW</legend>
        <label>Height (ft):</label>
        <input id="heightFeetInput" type="number" name="heightfeet" required="true" onchange="calculateBMR()" value="5">
        <label>(in):</label>
        <input id="heightInchesInput" type="number" name="heightinches" required="true" onchange="calculateBMR()" value="7"> <br /><br />
        <label>Age:</label>
        <input id="ageInput" type="number" name="age" min="0" max="120" required="true" onchange="calculateBMR()" value="28"></br></br>
        <label>Weight:</label>
        <input id="weightlbsInput" type="number" name="weightlbs" required="true" onchange="calculateBMR()" value="170"></br></br>
        <label>Select Gender:</label>
        <br />
        <input id="gender" type="radio" name="gender" value="male" checked> Male<br>
        <input id="gender" type="radio" name="gender" value="female"> Female<br>
        <input id="gender" type="radio" name="gender" value="other"> Other
        <br /><br />
        <label>How many hours of exercise do you get a week?</label>
        <br />
        <form id="exerciseForm">
        <input  type="radio" name="selectedexercise" value="1.2" checked> 1-3<br>
        <input  type="radio" name="selectedexercise" value="1.35"> 4-6<br>
        <input  type="radio" name="selectedexercise" value="1.5" > 6+
      </form>
        <br /><br /><br />
        <button id="calculate" class="btn-lg btn-success" type="button" onclick="displayBMR()">Calculate BMR</button>
        <button id="clearBMR" class="btn-lg btn-warning" type="button">Clear</button>
        <br /><br />
        <div id="displayBMR"></div>
        <div id="displayWeightLoss"></div>
        <div id="displayLeanGain"></div>
      </fieldset>
    </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
